parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver's side seat bracket can cause the seat to become detached from the frame, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The seat leans or tilts when sat in
the seat breaks or collapses while driving
the seat bracket or bolts break off
the front corner of the seat is not attached to the frame.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and rupture of brake lines can cause a sudden loss of brake function, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brakes feel spongy or soft
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking
the brake warning light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wipers can reduce visibility during rainy or snowy conditions, increasing the risk of accidents and compromising vehicle safety.
symptoms: The windshield wipers do not turn on
the windshield wipers move slowly or erratically
the windshield wipers leave streaks or residue on the windshield
the windshield wipers make unusual noises or vibrations.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Denial of Reimbursement for Windshield Wiper Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The denial of reimbursement for windshield wiper failure can lead to financial burdens on vehicle owners, who may be forced to pay out-of-pocket for repairs or replacements.
symptoms: Vehicle owners are denied reimbursement for windshield wiper repairs or replacements
despite the existence of a recall notice (98V-150).

the vehicle is unable to restart.
